To write the ratio \(2:1.8\) as a fraction,
\[
\frac{2}{1.8}
= \frac{2\cdot10}{1.8\cdot10}
= \frac{20}{18}
= \frac{10}{9}.
\]
So the simplified fraction is \(\displaystyle \tfrac{10}{9}.\)

To express the ratio \(2\tfrac13\) to \(5\tfrac14\) as a fraction,

1. Convert to improper fractions:  
   \(2\tfrac13 = \tfrac{7}{3},\quad 5\tfrac14 = \tfrac{21}{4}.\)

2. Form the quotient and simplify:  
   \[
     \frac{2\tfrac13}{5\tfrac14}
     = \frac{\tfrac{7}{3}}{\tfrac{21}{4}}
     = \frac{7}{3}\times\frac{4}{21}
     = \frac{28}{63}
     = \frac{4}{9}.
   \]

Answer: \(\displaystyle \tfrac{4}{9}.\)

